1. Observation practice:
observing group or individual lessons in music school and analysing them. Filling out practice diary and report.
2. Practice lessons: aim is to practice together with mentor.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of pedagogical practice is to integrate the educational and pedagogic knowledge of students in the reality of a music school; applied form of acquiring instrument teaching skills the main tasks of which are to * integrate theoretical knowledge and pedagogical skills of instrument teaching; * acknowledge the role(s) of a teacher in a real music school in its social and cultural context today; * develop self-consciousness of the student and motivate theoretical studies; * develop the perception of differences due to individuality of students in instructing their creative work, the skills to choose personal sub methodology. Observation practice at a music school: getting an overview of the work of an instrument teacher and of the organization of music school life. 
To widen and develop teaching practices got from the first part of pedagogical practice. Do teach how to motivate and disciplinate groups. To widen and develop instrument teaching skills through practical activity.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course a student:
1.	Has an overview of the work of a musical instrument teacher in music school.
2.	Knows the acts and laws that regulate the functioning of music schools in Estonia.
3.	Analyses the teaching and learning or musical instrument in different age groups.
4.     Analyses different pedagogical situations in group lesson; 
5.     Creates suitable study environment;
6.     Can understand individual, age-related and personal traits when preparing and analysing instrumental lessons;
7.     Analyses constantly his/her career as a teacher and plans his/her pedagogical career;
8.     Involved other students and parents in planning studies;
9.    Knows and practices different individual and group teaching methods.
